Title: Allied Precision 742G Bucket Heater
Reviews: ['It does heat a bucket pretty good. Not in minutes, but in the course of several minutes. Wont heat up the bathtub hardly. Uses a lot of power. The product should put better labeling on it... Or at least in a manual. My brother burnt himself picking it up. Also, it fails to show how to properly immerse it. Is it supposed to stand up or can it float on its side? Is there a water level limit? Can the handle be submerged. The plastic part is the handle, right?', 'I wanted a bucket heater that keeps the water from freezing over in a livestock bucket.  The instructions that came with it said to not submerge this heater into a bucket or receptacle that cannot handle "boiling water".  It said the heater will maintain that temperature and the auto turn off valve will prevent the temperature from dropping too low to freeze.  So, I plugged it into a 5 gallon bucket of water and it heated up way too hot for any animal to want to drink it.  I then put it in a 25 gallon bucket and the same thing happened, although not boiling, was still too hot for any pasture animal to drink.  The box showed a horse on it and I can tell  you right now, none of my horses drink hot coffee, tea, OR plain water.  I have no idea what purpose this heater has and when I called to report it there was no one there at the time to help me and I was promised  call back to discuss the findings.  No call ever came.  I would like to return it but refuse to pay return shipping on such a ridiculous product.  I will shop elsewhere.SJH', 'This works well for small bodies of water.  It was in a 25 gallon water tank for 24 hours and was just warm.  The ambient temperature was 55 degrees.  I was thinking it would be at a boil way before that, after reading the description.  I guess it is only 1000 watts.  It will work well to maintain the temperature, it just takes a while to get there.', 'Heats 5 gallon bucket of water to low oil in under 30 minutes. Well made product. I would purchase again.', "For the price this is a great product. I recommend hooking it up to a INK BIRD ITC-308 I believe it's called. It makes a great combo for reptiles or fish Very large fish tanks. ", 'So far i bought 2 of these.for the time that i had these, i really like them.only had a fee months but work great in 3 gallon buckets! 30 minutes  and water is hot.', 'I just put a little fountain water pump laying sideways in the pot I have it in, to circulate the water. It works perfectly.', 'Works perfect when I need hot  water at my shop. ', 'This unit really heats up the water. I added a water heater thermostat on the side of the bucket to keep the temps in the range I wanted. 120 deg F to 130 deg F. Works very well.', 'just the right size for a small bucket of water, gets hot quick']

Reviews: ["Easy to install by following the simple instructions on the package.  Makes filling the 1 lb canister simple and quick. ", 'With the one pound propane tanks in the $3-4 range this is a real money saver.   I put the small tanks in the freezer overnight.  Made sure the twenty pound tank was 70-75 degrees. Reviews: ['Considering purchasing a wick online for my 20+ year old kerosene heater left me with some doubt if the offered product would be a good fit like the original size. I decided to give it a try since the price was attractive and very competitive with what I could find in a store. When the wick arrived,i carefully opened the package and as I took the wick out, it felt thick and of good quality. After installing it,filing the tank and waiting half hour or so, I then lit the heater. After a few minutes I got a nice even glow demonstrating I got a good purchase!Be advised, it takes patience to make sure the new wick is even after you arrange it around the burner . Press the wick from the inside so it catches the little "prickles" that hold it in position before you try to slide it down . As you do this, keep your eye on the top of the wick to see that it remains even at the top of the burner before you slide the whole thing back into the heater.The wick was accurately sized as described for my heater!Additionally, the product arrived promptly.', 'Just what I needed and easy to install and works just fine.Put in the New one and got rid of the old. Title: Handy Heater HEAT-MC12/4 Plug Outlet Speace Heater Tested
Reviews: ['I purchased this heater for a very specific purpose. I needed a small heater to dry out a wood window sill for a window located in a bathroom shower (long story). This heater satisfied all of my requirements which included: small enough to fit in the space between the storm window and double hung window, generate enough heat to dry the space without over heating, have a thermostat, and operate continuously for a prolonged period of time. I have not had any problems operating this unit on a heavy duty extension cord (not recommended in instructions). This unit will automatically turn on and off as it reaches the temperature you set for the unit. It produces just enough heat to satisfy my need. Criticisms regarding the 12 hour time limit can be resolved by plugging this unit into a timer. When the power is shut off and then back on, the unit will run again for 12 hours intervals solving the problem of having to be present to restart the unit. This unit must be suspended to prevent blockage of the air intake located on the bottom of the heater.', "Quality feels good, not cheap. Plug rotation feature is secure and not wobbly or junky at all. Heater pulls 297 watts when running, but pulls ~750 watts for about 30 seconds when you turn it on from cold. This is a powerful little heater, you would not want to put your hand directly in front of it for very long. Definitely enough to heat a very small space like a car, or heat up a small room which isn't quite warm enough. Has a thermostat which works well. The heater will run the fan for a bit and cycle down just as it should. It has a red LED which always stays on and give the impression of a hot surface so that you don't forget that the grill could still be hot.The heater sucks air in from the bottom where the fan is.Honestly, this thing has better construction and features than most space heaters I've owned.Cannot yet speak to reliability but based on the good circuit design it should last quite a long time.", 'We have an L shaped bath room and the  baseboard heater is on the long side. On cold days the far corner of the short side gets cold.  This gadget is perfect, set temperature and  shave in comfort. easy to use, takes no space. I saved about  $1200 by not adding another baseboard floor heater when  a $12 heater is perfect.  Kudos to the designer for a great product !!Ol George', 'I wanted this for a very small seedling starter greenhouse but will be unable to use it as it shuts off after 12 hours.  Also when you turn it back on it starts at 90 degrees.  You have to reset the temp and timer every time you turn it back on.  I also bought one for my daughter to use in her tack room for two barn cats but she is also disappointed because of the 12 hour turn off feature.  Only useful if you are there to turn it back on and reset every 12 hours.', 'While this thinks key feature is size, It works well.  Unfortunately the the other plug in a two receptacle outlet cannot be used while this is plugged in.  It blocks the free receptacle partially enough to render it non-usable. It does produce some small fast heat to a rathed general localized area. Is it worth $20.00?  Yes if you will use often, no if you dont require the convenience of it.  Cheaper and more effective heaters are available, its really based on the buyers preference and intended use.  Works great for heating up bathroom when done with showering.  I would reccomend this if you find yourself seeing it  be applicable in a scenario.  ', 'This is a great heater for a small area.I plan on using it for a walk in closet that seems to not get heated very well.I can turn this little guy on for five minutes or so and the problem is solved', 'Better than i expected because the plug works both ways into the outlet, this is good 4 me cause all my outlets are upside down & heater has timer , & low & high..  compact & small, low price i really thinks thats great.  Thx.', 'I love the fact that these heaters have a ground connection.  The third pole helps stabilize the heater in the socket and keeps it from leaning and possibly falling out, like the socket heaters with only two poles.  They are great for a small room like a bathroom. ', "It is very small but it put out some nice heat for it's size.  I like the thermostat feature so it goes off when it gets to that temperature. Reviews: ['Considering purchasing a wick online for my 20+ year old kerosene heater left me with some doubt if the offered product would be a good fit like the original size. I decided to give it a try since the price was attractive and very competitive with what I could find in a store. When the wick arrived,i carefully opened the package and as I took the wick out, it felt thick and of good quality. After installing it,filing the tank and waiting half hour or so, I then lit the heater. After a few minutes I got a nice even glow demonstrating I got a good purchase!Be advised, it takes patience to make sure the new wick is even after you arrange it around the burner . Press the wick from the inside so it catches the little "prickles" that hold it in position before you try to slide it down . As you do this, keep your eye on the top of the wick to see that it remains even at the top of the burner before you slide the whole thing back into the heater.The wick was accurately sized as described for my heater!Additionally, the product arrived promptly.', 'Just what I needed and easy to install and works just fine.Put in the New one and got rid of the old. Title: Handy Heater HEAT-MC12/4 Plug Outlet Speace Heater
Reviews: ['I purchased this heater for a very specific purpose. I needed a small heater to dry out a wood window sill for a window located in a bathroom shower (long story). This heater satisfied all of my requirements which included: small enough to fit in the space between the storm window and double hung window, generate enough heat to dry the space without over heating, have a thermostat, and operate continuously for a prolonged period of time. I have not had any problems operating this unit on a heavy duty extension cord (not recommended in instructions). This unit will automatically turn on and off as it reaches the temperature you set for the unit. It produces just enough heat to satisfy my need. Criticisms regarding the 12 hour time limit can be resolved by plugging this unit into a timer. When the power is shut off and then back on, the unit will run again for 12 hours intervals solving the problem of having to be present to restart the unit. This unit must be suspended to prevent blockage of the air intake located on the bottom of the heater.', "Quality feels good, not cheap. Plug rotation feature is secure and not wobbly or junky at all. Heater pulls 297 watts when running, but pulls ~750 watts for about 30 seconds when you turn it on from cold. This is a powerful little heater, you would not want to put your hand directly in front of it for very long. Definitely enough to heat a very small space like a car, or heat up a small room which isn't quite warm enough. Has a thermostat which works well. The heater will run the fan for a bit and cycle down just as it should. It has a red LED which always stays on and give the impression of a hot surface so that you don't forget that the grill could still be hot.The heater sucks air in from the bottom where the fan is.Honestly, this thing has better construction and features than most space heaters I've owned.Cannot yet speak to reliability but based on the good circuit design it should last quite a long time.", 'We have an L shaped bath room and the  baseboard heater is on the long side. On cold days the far corner of the short side gets cold.  This gadget is perfect, set temperature and  shave in comfort. easy to use, takes no space. I saved about  $1200 by not adding another baseboard floor heater when  a $12 heater is perfect.  Kudos to the designer for a great product !!Ol George', 'I wanted this for a very small seedling starter greenhouse but will be unable to use it as it shuts off after 12 hours.  Also when you turn it back on it starts at 90 degrees.  You have to reset the temp and timer every time you turn it back on.  I also bought one for my daughter to use in her tack room for two barn cats but she is also disappointed because of the 12 hour turn off feature.  Only useful if you are there to turn it back on and reset every 12 hours.', 'While this thinks key feature is size, It works well.  Unfortunately the the other plug in a two receptacle outlet cannot be used while this is plugged in.  It blocks the free receptacle partially enough to render it non-usable. It does produce some small fast heat to a rathed general localized area. Is it worth $20.00?  Yes if you will use often, no if you dont require the convenience of it.  Cheaper and more effective heaters are available, its really based on the buyers preference and intended use.  Works great for heating up bathroom when done with showering.  I would reccomend this if you find yourself seeing it  be applicable in a scenario.  ', 'This is a great heater for a small area.I plan on using it for a walk in closet that seems to not get heated very well.I can turn this little guy on for five minutes or so and the problem is solved', 'Better than i expected because the plug works both ways into the outlet, this is good 4 me cause all my outlets are upside down & heater has timer , & low & high..  compact & small, low price i really thinks thats great.  Thx.', 'I love the fact that these heaters have a ground connection.  The third pole helps stabilize the heater in the socket and keeps it from leaning and possibly falling out, like the socket heaters with only two poles.  They are great for a small room like a bathroom. ', "It is very small but it put out some nice heat for it's size.  I like the thermostat feature so it goes off when it gets to that temperature.  ", 'Iâve given 5 of these as gifts. They are perfect for a bathroom or office or reading area. They are powerful but only heat a small area. Buy using it in the morning by my chair while I read the paper or file paperwork I do not have to turn up my furnace. I can pre heat a bathroom when itâs below zero outside and avoid freezing the second I step out of the shower!Not intended to warm large rooms. ']

Title: Vornado VH203 Personal Heater & Gold-Compact Cool Touch Electric 750w
Reviews: ["This item is functional as a fan but the heater settings are not very hot.  The only real advantage of this item is that the lower electricity usage keeps the cord & electric plug from becoming dangerously hot and melting your electric outlet (like with other heaters  1000W).  Other than that I can't really say much else about this item.  Since my bed area is just an open space in the men's dorm of my recuperative care shelter I have no idea if these machines can really circulate the air in a small enclosedspace.  I am glad to have two of them though because my bed is right under a vent duct in the ceiling and with the AC over functioning I get a lot of cold air blowing on me at all hours.  But I'm basically sleeping with the heaters in my bed on high because of the weaker heat settings.  Caveat empetor.", 'Great personal heater, fairly quiet (white noise, basically), perfect for a small space like on an office desk or while sitting on the sofa.  Not recommended for heating a larger room, but for personal use it canât be beat.  Also very easy to move with you, unlike the tower style heaters that are very common in the market.  It has a lower setting too, which can come in handy because in a small setting (on the sofa), it can get you warmed up very quickly on high.', 'Nice heater for the money. This is my second one...great for small areas. ', 'GREAT desk fan and heater!  I like the fact it has a shut off feature if it tips over.  I loved it so much that I bought another for a different work place.  Highly recommend!', "One blade on the fan was broken during shipment.I used a soldering iron to melt it back on. Doesn't heat like I thought it would.Its ok for small bathroom .", 'Light weight, takes little space to store.  Works perfect for small areas.', 'This is a nice personal heater.  If you want a little heat for your personal space, it does the trick.', 'The heater works well for a small room.  The fan without the heat is weak.', 'This was a replacement of one that quit working these are great little heaters that work and heat in small areas']
